Autoprefixer is a PostCSS plugin that automatically adds vendor prefixes 
(like -webkit-, -moz-, -ms-, -o-) to your CSS rules,
 based on the browsers you want to support (as defined in your .browserslistrc file). 
This helps your CSS work correctly across different browsers without manually writing all the prefixes.

Example:

If you write this CSS:

.user-select {
  user-select: none;
}

Autoprefixer will output:

.user-select {
  -webkit-user-select: none;
  -moz-user-select: none;
  -ms-user-select: none;
  user-select: none;
}

Summary:
Autoprefixer saves you time and ensures cross-browser compatibility
by automatically adding the necessary vendor prefixes to your CSS.